      "id": "RQ-0010",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Clarify PID-lock staleness policy for PID reuse edge cases",
      "description": "Audit notes PID-based liveness checks cannot detect PID recycling; timestamp staleness mitigates implicitly. Add an explicit, documented policy in `lock/stale.rs` (e.g. age-based escalation when `started_at` is inconsistent with observed liveness) so operators understand behavior in the narrow TOCTOU window. Outcome: lock behavior is predictable and defensible under PID reuse.\n\nValidation: `inspect_existing_lock` marks stale only when `pid_liveness(owner.pid).is_definitely_not_running()` (`stale.rs`); `pid.rs` documents indeterminate liveness as conservative. There is no explicit narrative tying PID reuse / `started_at` to operator-visible guarantees in `stale.rs` today beyond the `(STALE PID)` message path.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "audit",
        "lock",
        "correctness"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/lock/pid.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/lock/stale.rs",
